trend_summary: Across the sequence the suburb gains floor area: warehouses and offices fill parcels along the highway, new neighbourhoods arise in wooded pockets, and road capacity expands. Although canopy remains extensive, incremental infill slightly reduces green coverage; a refurbished sports complex and fresh parkland diversify land use.
notable_changes: White-roofed industrial/logistics blocks expand along the central highway corridor, replacing vacant land.
Additional residential subdivisions appear in western and southern pockets, reducing continuous tree cover.
